deepLinks.name: English Language
deepLinks.snippet: English is a West Germanic language of the Indo-European language family, with its earliest forms spoken by the inhabitants of early medieval England. deepLinks.snippet: Caroline Agnes Brady (also known as Caroline Agnes Von Egmont Brady; October 3, 1905 – November 5, 1980) was an American philologist who specialised in Old English and Old Norse works.
